Hey brah, when cutting:

- Lower the volume of your training, you are weaker and recover slower so don't go hard as usual, use a more barebones routine without much volume
- Do bodyweight exercises, gains from them will stay after gaining back weight, pullups, chinups, dips etc

- Work in a bit higher rep ranges than usual, don't go for 3 or 1 rep maxes etc.
- For cutting is best to use intermittent fasting, it's good
- Don't do exercises that are too heavy on your CNS like deadlift, rack pull...
Best use a routine like upper/lower, PPL, whatever you want really, but aim for 3-4 gym visits max, mroe than than and it will get too hard

Seek closed doors, go where no one goes, stay in liminal spaces. Read illegal texts, watch things you're not supposed to watch, reach states of thought that are anomalous. Find the border of reality and run into it repeatedly.
